<moral_forms>
    Moral matter <html:a href='/theorist/ethics/moral_matter/way.xht#M'>M</html:a> has two essential forms
    <cog:comprising>
        <G cog:lid='G'>Relating the personal to the endmost goal of the person</G>
        <F cog:lid='F'>Promoting a maximum, universal sum of personal freedom</F>
        </cog:comprising>
    <formal_necessity cog:lid='formal_necessity'>
        Apparently G and F are formally necessary to M
        <_>
            G thoroughly entangles M
            <σ xmlns='data:,wayscript.bit.step'><html:i>- finish scripting this -</html:i></σ>
            </_>
        <_>
            F thoroughly entangles M
            <σ xmlns='data:,wayscript.bit.step'><html:i>- finish scripting this -</html:i></σ>
            </_>
        </formal_necessity>
    <instrumental_fitness cog:lid='instrumental_fitness'>
        Apparently G and F are instrumentally necessary and sufficient to M
        <_ cog:lid='E_from_GF'>
            Instituting G and F appears to be necessary and sufficient to E
            <cog:comprising>
                <_>Instituting G seems prudently indispensible as a means to E</_>
                <_>Instituting F seems prudently indispensible as a means to E</_>
                <_>The combined institution of G and F seems to lack nothing as a means to E</_>
                </cog:comprising>
            <σ xmlns='data:,wayscript.bit.step'><html:i>- finish scripting this -</html:i></σ>
            </_>
        <_>
            E is the aim of M
            <M cog:link='/theorist/ethics/moral_matter/#M' id='M'/>
            <E cog:link='/theorist/ethics/moral_matter/#E'/>
            </_>
        </instrumental_fitness>



    </moral_forms>



